section.def:
pre-existing registered PIE auditor
                (原有註冊公眾利益實體核數師) means a person registered as a
            registered PIE auditor under the pre-amended Ordinance;

paragraph.content:
before the transition date, the name of an individual was recorded in the
                former PIE auditors register as a responsible person of a pre-existing registered
                PIE auditor;

a pre-existing registered PIE auditor proposed before the transition date
                    to add the name of a person to the list of registered responsible persons of the
                    auditor under section 20Y of the pre-amended Ordinance;

a pre-existing registered PIE auditor proposed before the transition date to
                add the name of a person to the list of registered responsible persons of the
                auditor under section 20Y of the pre-amended Ordinance;

the HKICPA Council decided before the transition date to revoke or suspend
                    a pre-existing PIE auditor registration under section 20T or
                        20X of the pre-amended Ordinance;

subsection.def:
section 20T decision (第20T條決定) means a decision made under
                    section 20T of the pre-amended Ordinance to revoke or suspend a
                pre-existing PIE auditor registration;

paragraph.content:
before the transition date, a pre-existing registered PIE auditor was required
                under section 20Z or 20ZA of the pre-amended Ordinance to
                inform the HKICPA Council of a change;

section.def:
deemed practising certificate
                                (視同執業證書)—see sections
                                24(1) and 26(4);

deemed CPA(P) partnership firm
                                (視同執業會計師合夥事務所)—see sections
                                33(1) and 35(2)(b);

deemed CPA(P) sole proprietor
                                (視同獨營執業會計師)—see sections
                                32(1) and 35(2)(a);

subsection.def:
conclusion report (完結報告), in relation to a practice review, means a report made under
                    section 32C(3) of the pre-amended PAO at the conclusion of the
                review;

subparagraph.content:
the Investigation Committee has informed the HKICPA Council that in its
                        opinion there is a prima facie case against the person investigated;
                        but

paragraph.content:
before the transition date, a complaint was made to the HKICPA Registrar
                    under section 34(1) of the pre-amended PAO about any PAO misconduct;
                    but

the order may be appealed against under section 41 of the
                    pre-amended PAO as if the 2021 Amending Ordinance had not come into
                    operation;

for the purposes of section 20AAZJ(1) of the amended Ordinance,
                    the registration is taken to be revoked under section 37CA(2)(d)(i)
                    of the amended Ordinance.

for the purposes of section 20AAZJ(1) of the amended Ordinance,
                    the registration is taken to be revoked under section 37CA(2)(d)(i)
                    of the amended Ordinance.

for the purposes of section 20AAZZD(1) of the amended Ordinance,
                    the registration is taken to be revoked under section 37CA(2)(d)(i)
                    of the amended Ordinance.

subparagraph.content:
the name of a company that was a corporate practice under the
                        pre-amended PAO before the name was removed from the former CPA register;
                        and

to produce or provide to the AFRC a document or information in
                        connection with the registration of the company as a corporate practice;
                        or

paragraph.content:
a reference to the Council in the 2019 pre-amended Ordinance (that
                            Ordinance) is to be construed as a reference to the
                    AFRC;

in section 2(1) of that Ordinance, the definition of
                            specified enforcement agency is to be construed as if
                    paragraph (c) of that definition were repealed;

section 36(1)(c) of that Ordinance is to be construed as
                    excluding referral of the case concerned under section 9(f) of that
                    Ordinance to the HKICPA;

subsection.def:
2019 pre-amended Ordinance (《2019年原有本條例》) means the Ordinance as in force
                immediately before the 2019 Ordinance commencement
                    date*;

subparagraph.content:
any pending proposal made by a registered PIE auditor under the
                        pre-amended Ordinance to add an additional registered responsible
                        person;

any matter that is being dealt with under section 20T or
                            20X of the pre-amended Ordinance at the transition time;
                        and
